	(text "The circuit layout you have constructed for the LM2596S-ADJ step-down regulator on pcb-journal features a highly functional configuration designed for versatile voltage management. It operates across a wide input voltage range VIN spanning from 4.5V up to 40V,\nthough maintaining an input between 7V and 35V is strongly recommended to ensure long-term stability and optimal efficiency under load conditions. To guarantee stable and consistent regulation at the output, the design relies on a dropout voltage margin\nwhere the input voltage must remain at least 1.5 higher than the target output ($V_{IN} \\geq V_{OUT} + 1.5\\text{V}$).On the output side, utilizing the adjustable version of the IC alongside the onboard potentiometer ($RV1$) allows the output voltage\n($V_{OUT}$) to be customized and precisely tuned from $1.23\\text{V}$ up to $37\\text{V}$. In terms of load capacity, this specific setup can continuously deliver an output current of up to $2\\text{A}$ without requiring external cooling elements.\n Furthermore, if the PCB implementation utilizes a proper thermal copper zone or an added external heatsink, the system's capacity can safely expand to handle a maximum output current of up to $3\\text{A}$."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
